_json.gridTitle: Most people have come to the point where they say, “Well I don’t need doctrine. I don’t need theology. I just love Jesus.  That is a foolish statement.  - Justin Peters
_json.description: Justin Peters is a man who suffers from what he describes as a moderate form of Cerebral Palsy (or CP as he often refers to it). Peters has a Master of Divinity and also a Master of Theology. Both from Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary. He is passionate about what the Word says and about opposing the people who twist it and take it out of context to serve themselves. He has great knowledge of the Word and on the Word of Faith movement.
